The paper introduces a motion planning system for high degree-of-freedom robots, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The system incorporates probabilistic methods and estimation techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of optimization and risk allocation approaches, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
